The epidemic has plunged us into anxiety and fear, and many of us would rather go back to work and return to the familiar rhythms and busyness of idleness at home. Today's letter is from a poetry lover, closed at home days, Ta write poetry, reading poetry, to capture a bit of poetry suppressed in life. The poetry continued after Ta returned to work.

If the sky only cast iron

By Suri

On Feb. 13, a friend sent an ID of a live studio on a live broadcast website, saying that he would be welcome to come in at 9:30 to watch a small poetry reading with eight people live, and that he would also read a few poems.

When the time came, the studio was sealed, and many times, finally in one place successfully read a mouthful. The form of the Poetry Club is that everyone takes turns broadcasting live from their home, which is spread all over the country.

It took a little bit of a turn, but it worked out. But the mood that followed the cancellations and rejections never left people's minds, and someone showered them with gifts.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Beijing, February 14,2020

I remember when I was a kid, I had a school trip to the park, and I wasn't allowed to bring snacks, but I secretly hid my candy beans in my pants. They came in a clear, soft plastic box shaped like a pistol. While playing on the slide, jellybean's tiny lid was pushed open and fell out of his pants. The teacher confiscated it on the spot.

Without hesitation, I got off the slide and said I had to go to the bathroom. On the lawn outside the bathroom door, pull out the remaining jelly beans from your pants pockets and slowly break them down. I always remember the feeling at that time, I am very rich fans, so very distressed by the confiscated candy bean (was thrown away by the teacher) , I am also quite realistic, treat the remaining few can also try to adjust the mood, to a more enjoyable attitude to taste.

We've all had childhood experiences where toys were hidden, snacks were confiscated, and Television wasn't allowed, and we've all had to hide our toys before they were hidden, and take the last bite of ice cream before entering the house, listen to the sound of your parents coming home on the stairs and turn off the TV.

Grow Up, want to read a few favorite sentences to get resonance, appreciate the beauty of sharing, but also to experience a journey. It is one of the many and varied desires of human beings, to eat, to love, to flatter, to play, to have fun, to express, to read.

On New Year's Eve, I posted a poem I had written that night on my public account, nightroad notes, and then I leaned by my bed, waiting for the new year. At the turn of the calendar year and the New Year, there was not the slightest noise of fireworks outside the window, the buildings were strangely silent, the streets were deserted, although the street lights were brilliant.

I made a phone call to my friend far away, my eyes were wet when I spoke, I said I was afraid, if it was me, if it would be me one day.

At the time, I tried to read it to her, but it didn't quite work out

The World of yesterday

Written on New Year's Eve 2019, revised on February 20

Old Is the cloud flying snow relies on the wall to forget the old people to cry, the wild smoke curl up to gather and scatter to spell out a requiem

Some people pity me luxuriant do not love to sing a short song, discard what more to take away more

So I looked at the lonely mountain, the setting sun burning can not find me, the wind blowing stars motionless and shaking like me

The Voice of the throat cry disappeared, you will not laugh always someone taught you sentimental but always seems to be ruthless art of life

The son Geng yellow month strides into the gate building, the new matter old time the human shadow flickering star straight stares at my eye

I still miss you even though I know death is not real

A word of truth pressed against my chest

With a constant patience and love make a heart still look forward to the summer evening breeze

And Moses parted the Red Sea from Egypt, and he that hath a withered hand shall stretch out his staff into the sea

So each occupied their own positions, in the new and old alternate midnight take-off

In the pure body of the earth, I lick the drizzle of the universe's vibration

Drench me, drench me, destroy me, and give me an apocalyptic thrill

Comfort me

Take pity on me

Touch it for me

I'm the one lusting after a night of drinking in the arms of a loved one

Knock over the glasses. That's me on the other side

Loneliness was thrown into the fire box, burning out the stars is me

The stars must be small enough to be bright enough, and they don't shine just to talk to themselves

As long as the stars are alive,

A star can talk to another light-year away

The world of yesterday is old and new

Look at the stars there are countless farewell to nothing, thousands of miles to meet

Spring, continuous snow

Early in the morning, I pulled back the curtains to find the snow, the road was empty, the sun was dim, the sky was white.

The phone's ringing. It's my mom. In the video, she cuts open a Purple Passion Flower and praises me for "helping farmers by eating" , which is better than what she got on her trip to Guangxi.

"someone called me several times last night, just received, said is selling passion fruit, let me pass the scale, see if there is less, " my mother said.

Fruit enough to weigh, my mother was deeply moved, told me, "must give a good comment, and buy a few pounds. "

I cut open the order on Taobao and looked closely at the delivery place: Dehong Dai and Jingpo Autonomous Prefecture.

Out of curiosity, I looked up this place: "De" for below, and "macro" for Salween River, meaning: downstream from Salween River. The Dai and Jingpo Autonomous Prefecture is located in the southwest border area, in the western part of Yunnan Province, on the sino-myanmar border.

I imagined the passionflower my mother had eaten growing healthily in the valley jungle, until it had matured, in a winter-free, rain-filled place.

In the store's product details page, a large flock of hens roamed beneath passion fruit trees: Chickens raised in orchards, free range local chickens, and the ability to pick up pests and provide the fruit trees with natural nutrients.

The foodie farmers placed five orders, and not every one of them went smoothly.

A few days ago, an order logistics display for Hainan mango was about to arrive in Beijing, but it was suddenly sent back to the place of delivery. The shop owner replied that due to insufficient manpower, the first batch of goods could not be checked in the links of picking, sorting and delivery, product size is inconsistent, green fruit is not ripe and part of the phenomenon of frostbite, so the need to "recall. ".

FRUITS, vegetables, flowers... there is a forest in front of my eyes now. Everything is trembling slightly with the huge world, but someone will bury the seeds of the New Year in the soil, waiting for them to germinate and bloom without knowing it.

Like plants, they also have animal hair.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A cat basks in the sun in a residential area on December 12,2019

Community downstairs, dusk, a girl skillfully took a cage cover away a kitten (cat obediently drilling cage) : "It looks like it is not a wild cat, you carefully look at its body, to heat... take back to take care of. "

Back to work. Change Water for a bamboo

On the afternoon of February 14, an e-mail from the company arrived at each colleague's e-mail address. After much discussion, the company finally decided to start with a small number of people, next week gradually restore the office. Group colleagues shift, 50% of the daily staff on duty.

On my first day back, I put on a thick sweater and down jacket, packed a kettle, a bottle of alcohol, lunch, my usual allergy medicine, put on a comfortable mask, and rode out.

The electric calf was borrowed from a friend the day before. There were more pedestrians on the road than in the past few days. A lady who looked like she was going to work passed me by on her bicycle, the scent of skin care products was caught in my nose through the air and my mask.

Arriving at the office, my new mom friend posted a message after she had tidied up: a month later, I was sitting in my office again, breathing out my chest and saying, Yay!

You know, with your family and your kids, everybody wants a chance to breathe. "Every day, we test each other's limits, " she said.

Sitting at his desk and looking around, it seems that the office is not much different than it was years ago, except for a decrease in the density of people. When people can make eye contact, they don't talk. "when the epidemic is over, our eyes will be brighter. "

But something's changed.

Two years ago, the former boss back to Germany bought a large number of transfer bamboo, the number is the head of the department, I hope everyone can "thrive" , at this moment, it collective scorched yellow leaves took my eyes..

Almost jumping out of my chair, I ran to change the water for them.

Back to work together, as well as friends of the small micro-enterprises.

He did not complain, except when asked, "business is not good. ". For him, it was still a "New Year" , eager for personal progress, eager to grow the company, eager to "do more, faster. ".

He told me that the company recently interviewed a child learning Chinese, the other side said that they like poetry, like a variety of many poets, let her take an example, the child was silent for a long time, "thought in the brewing of a shocking name. " And finally, the name of the Robert Frost. "Lately, I feel poetry is so far away from my life, " she added, a little choked

"I know Frost, you sent me his verse, " said the friend.

I remember that, too. It was Going for water:

Notloth to have excuse to go……We run as if to meet the moon.

Glad to have an excuse to go out... as we ran as if to meet the moon.

Not only does the epidemic have a profound impact on our lives today, it will also occupy our memories and change our minds for a long time to come. We need more eyes to continue to observe and document the crises and changes of our time. These are sincere and weighty records, and we will keep them.
